while performing and analysing this E-Commerce Sales project, these were the Project Findings :


Clothing was the most popular category, generating the highest number of sales and the highest overall revenue.

Outerwear recorded the lowest sales, making it the least purchased category during the analysis period.

Young Adult customers contributed the highest revenue, showing that this age group was the most active in shopping.

Montana, Illinois, and California generated the highest purchase revenue, while Kansas recorded the lowest overall sales.

Most customers did not have a subscription, indicating an opportunity to improve customer retention through membership programs.

The average purchase amount remained around $60, showing that customers generally spent a similar amount per order.

The average customer review rating was 3.75, suggesting that customers were generally satisfied but there is still room to improve the shopping experience.

The dashboard helped identify customer buying patterns, product category performance, and revenue trends, providing valuable insights to support better inventory planning and business decisions.
